$ System.Byte (struct)

`System.Byte` represents an 8-bit unsigned integer.

In the → Microsoft/dot-net terminology, a sequence of bytes is referred to as *stream*. The base class for all streams is → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/Stream[`System.IO.Stream`].

In → Windows/PowerShell, the → Windows/PowerShell/language/lexical-structure/token/literal#ps-int-literal-datatype[data type suffix for integers] to indicate a (signed) `Byte` is `y`, the suffix for an
unsigned byte is `uy`:
code {
PS C:\> (42y).GetType().FullName
System.SByte
PS C:\> (42uy).GetType().FullName
System.Byte
System.SByte
code }

sa:
  → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/_integral-numeric-types
